summary: Taylor Swift's self-titled debut album was released in 2006. She wrote or co-wrote all the songs about teenage life, love, and friendships. The country album features acoustic instruments and pop sounds. It was a big success, with two number-one country singles and a nomination for Album of the Year. Swift promoted it on Myspace, reaching a young audience. The album's honest lyrics and country-pop style influenced her future music and other artists. It's considered one of the best debut albums ever.
title: Taylor Swift (album)
